National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Nigerian Presidential Chief of Staff Professor Ibrahim Gambari and Nigerian National Security Advisor Babagana Monguno at the White House. They discussed collaborating to address global challenges such as the COVID-19 pandemic, the global economy, and the climate crisis. They also expressed concerns about democratic backsliding and political instability in West Africa and discussed efforts to restore constitutional order in Burkina Faso, Guinea, and Mali. Sullivan expressed US support for Nigeria's preparations for free and fair elections in 2023 and their efforts to counter violent extremists and terrorist groups.